 East London - The safety and security cluster is in full swing in Buffalo City led by the South African Police Services, the Buffalo City Municipality said on Wednesday. "The cluster is comprised of various stakeholders including traffic and law enforcement, fire and disaster management," it described. "This week, the cluster also welcomed members of the South African National Defense Force. "This is to conduct duties in terms of the Disaster Management Act.57/2002 Regulation 27( 2) Officers/ Members to focus on compliance Enforcement of the above Act and the directives of Nationwide Lock down." According to the Metro, there are roadblocks being conducted on all entrance/ exit routes in Buffalo City. Some of the Safety Operations conducted over the weekend reflected as follows: Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 